comands:

python3 - interactive interpreter
.py -- save files with this extension
cat -- shows the contents of a file on linux

example:
cat /home/cleyton/ProjetosGit/msc_thesis_naea_ufpa/download_pdfiles.py  

execute a script calling the pipeline interpreter:

python3 dir/download_pdfiles.py

so, write "python3" each time you run cant get really old... so, write a first line in your code called "shebang":

to open a file, and not just read it, use "nano"

nano -- one of the editors available on a linux sys

example:
nano /home/cleyton/ProjetosGit/msc_thesis_naea_ufpa/download_pdfiles.py  

shebang: #!/usr/bin/env python3

chmod -- do the file executable (change us file permissions -- permissions are: read, write, and execute)

example:

chmod +x /home/cleyton/ProjetosGit/msc_thesis_naea_ufpa/download_pdfiles.py 

it's make the file can be execute usin dot slash

./ -- means thath file is located in any of the dir listed in the Path variable / represente the current directory

Path variable tells operating sys where to find programs to execute


